com.moblima.movie

Class Movie

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.moblima.movie.Movie

  • public class Movie
extends java.lang.Object
    Movie is an entity class. The class contains all the information related to an individual movie. The class contains methods to get and set the data of the movie object
    Author:
    Ivo Janssen

      • setRating

        @Deprecated
public void setRating(double newRating)
        Deprecated. 
        Sets the rating of a movie. No longer used, rating value is calculated based on the ratings given by the users. Every time getRating() is called the rating will automatically be updated to the actual average
        Parameters:
        newRating - new rating of the movie, this should be a double between 1.0 and 5.0

      • canBook

        public boolean canBook()
        Determines if the movie can be booked by users. Movies which have a status of "Coming Soon" or "End Of Showing" can not be booked by the moviegoers.
        Returns:
        boolean: can the movie be booked by a moviegoer.
